        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sasakwa, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Allen, Francis, Sasakwa, Gerty, Atwood, and Spaulding.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
